<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <p xml:id="PN334-intro">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. maturait tamiḻak kūttaṉār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PN334">
<l>kāmaru paḻaṉak kaṇpi ṉaṉṉa</l>
<l>tūmayirk kuṟuntā ṇeṭuñcevik kuṟumuyal</l>
<l>puṉṟalaic ciṟāar maṉṟat tārppiṟ</l>
<l>paṭappoṭuṅ kummē <gap quantity="5" unit="character" reason="lost"/>piṉpu<gap quantity="7" unit="character" reason="lost"/></l>
<l><gap quantity="29" unit="character" reason="lost"/>ṉūrē maṉaiyōḷ</l>
<l>pāṇa rārttavum paricila rōmpavu</l>
<l>mūṇoli yaravamoṭu kaitū vāḷē</l>
<l>yuyarmarup piyāṉaip pukarmukat taṇinta</l>
<l>polam<gap quantity="48" unit="character" reason="lost"/>p</l>
<l>paricil paricilark kīya</l>
<l>vuravuvēṟ kāḷaiyuṅ kaitū vāṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The little hare with long ears, short legs [and] white fur,</l>
<l>like the elephant grass by the lovely paddy field,</l>
<l>keeps itself to the garden(?)</l>
<l>when the little boys with ruddy heads make noise in the village common.</l>
<l>…………………… The lady of the house,</l>
<l>in order to feed bards and protect gift seekers</l>
<l>does not rest with the sound that comes [from making] food,</l>
<l>……. golden…………..</l>
<l>that adorn the spotted faces of elephants with high tusks……..</l>
<l>and the young man with a strong spear does not rest</l>
<l>in order to give gifts to those who seek them.</l>
</lg>
    </div>
